abstract: I wanted to uncover ancient shards of my childhood gender and piece them back into the whole.
snippet: I wanted to uncover ancient shards of my childhood gender and piece them back into the whole.
lead_paragraph: Two years ago, I spent Christmas with my family in North Carolina with a mission: to digitize a dozen or so of my favorite childhood photos.

headline_main: The Problem With Putting a Price on the End of the World

abstract: New York’s newest neighborhood drew inspiration from Battery Park City, but is filled with 21st-century twists.
snippet: New York’s newest neighborhood drew inspiration from Battery Park City, but is filled with 21st-century twists.
lead_paragraph: Land where there was none before. A careful ratio of places to live, work, eat and recline on lawns. A sense of being in New York, but not quite of it.

abstract: As more technology creeps into the front seat to help drivers, so too will systems that eavesdrop on and monitor them.
snippet: As more technology creeps into the front seat to help drivers, so too will systems that eavesdrop on and monitor them.
lead_paragraph: The automobile, in American life, has long been a hallmark of freedom. A teenager’s first driver’s license offers freedom from Mom and Dad. A new car and the open road bring the freedom to chase the American dream. But as more technology creeps in to help drivers, so, too, will systems that eavesdrop on and monitor them, necessitated not by convenience but by new safety concerns.

abstract: A documentary to be screened on Capitol Hill next month, in which I am featured, chronicles the experience of low-income students navigating college admissions.
snippet: A documentary to be screened on Capitol Hill next month, in which I am featured, chronicles the experience of low-income students navigating college admissions.
lead_paragraph: When I heard that federal prosecutors were charging 50 people in six states for a college admissions bribery scheme and read the accounts that followed, outlining all of the other extensive, mostly legal, help that applicants from rich families get, it underscored how different the admissions experience was for me and my high school classmates in Canarsie.

abstract: A look at the championship team captured in the 1969 Topps Baseball set.
snippet: A look at the championship team captured in the 1969 Topps Baseball set.
lead_paragraph: Tom Seaver won the rookie of the year award in 1967, finishing 16-13 for a Mets team that was still nowhere near .500. In 1969 he went 25-7 with a 2.21 E.R.A. and 18 complete games, astounding by current standards. He won the National League Cy Young Award that season, as he did again as a Met in 1973 and 1975. More than any other player, he set the tone for the Mets’ transformation into champions.

abstract: The special counsel’s decision not to take a position on whether President Trump’s norm-shattering actions constituted obstruction means future presidents will feel entitled to make similar moves.
snippet: The special counsel’s decision not to take a position on whether President Trump’s norm-shattering actions constituted obstruction means future presidents will feel entitled to make similar moves.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After Watergate, it was unthinkable that a president would fire an F.B.I. director who was investigating him or his associates. Or force out an attorney general for failing to protect him from an investigation. Or dangle pardons before potential witnesses against him.
